= Negotiations for a New Cabinet

On April 18 Sartono met to the President to report his failure as *formateur* and returned his mandate in forming a new cabinet. The President is to appoint a new *formateur*.

- @sukiman-sidik: The President has appointed Sidik Djojosukarto and Sukiman Wirjosandjojo..

@sukiman-sidik

The President has announced the names of two new *formateur*s, Sidik Djojosukarto, chairman of the <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span>, and Sukiman Wirjosandjojo, chairman of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> party council. The two are expected to form a "coalition cabinet on a broad national basis" in five days.

- @begin: Begin negotiations..

@begin
new-page: true
face-image: img/portraits/sukiman.jpeg

= Negotiations for a New Cabinet

The Natsir-led <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> executive council is shocked by the appointment of Sukiman, Natsir's arch-nemesis within the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> and its legislative chairman, as a cabinet *formateur*. Natsir and Sukiman came into frequent disagreements and heated debates during <span class="tooltip-text" title="The highest decision-making body of the Masjumi and other Islamic organizations. The equivalent of a congress.">*Muktamar*</span>s. The division between the highest decision-making bodies of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> has greatly hindered the development of the already heterogenous political organization. 

After some internal bickering the Natsir-led executive reluctantly endorsed Sukiman's acceptance of the *formateur*-ship with the condition that he must return his mandate if the five-day attempt is unsuccesful. This is great news for us, for Sukiman is more cooperative to the <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> and is more likely to accept a fair compromise than Natsir. 

There remained the old question however, of the distribution of seats and the Prime Ministership. It seems that the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> is still pressing their claim on the Prime Ministership, but maybe they are more open to compromises with Sukiman as their representative.

- @pni-concede: Let go of our claim of the Prime Ministership.
- @masjumi-concede: The <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> caves in to our demand.
- @compromise: Give the Prime Ministership to a third party as a compromise.
- @failure: The negotiations fail.

@pni-concede
unavailable-subtitle: Much of the party and Sidik himslef is against this.
choose-if: masyumi_relation >= 100

@masjumi-concede
unavailable-subtitle: The <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span>, even with Sukiman, continues to press their claim on the Prime Ministership.
choose-if: masyumi_relation >= 100

@compromise
subtitle: By continuing, we will accept a three-day extension offered by the President, possibly angering the Natsirite <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span>.
go-to: compromise-no if masyumi_relation < 40; compromise-yes if masyumi_relation >= 40

@compromise-no

Sukiman rejects our compromise proposal and urged the appointment of a <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> Prime Minister.

- @compromise2: Let the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> have the Prime Ministership as long as it is not Natsir.
- @failure

@compromise2
subtitle: This will increase dissent.

Sukiman has accepted our offer to appoint a non-Natsir member of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> to the Prime Ministership. Furthermore Sukiman agreed to the request of the President that he should accept the Prime Ministership.

- @sukiman-pm: Sukiman will become the Prime Minister.

@sukiman-pm
subtitle: <img src="img/icons/katolik.png" style="width: 30px;">

- @root

@compromise-yes

Sukiman has accepted our compromise proposal. Now we must who this third party will be.

- @assaat: Assaat
- @wongsonegoro: Wongsonegoro

@assaat
subtitle: Former acting President of the Republic of Indonesia and Minister of Internal Affairs in the Natsir cabinet.

Assaat is appointed as Prime Minister. Now we must select our ministries.

@wongsonegoro
subtitle: Former governor of Central Java, an experienced minister and leader of the <span style="color: #894400;">**PIR**</span>

Wongsonegoro is appointed as Prime Minister. Now we must select our ministries.

@failure
title: The negotiations fail.
subtitle: We have failed to come to an agreement.

It appears that the difficulties of bridging the two biggest opposing parties prove too great for Sidik and Sukiman. They are expected to return their mandate back to the President so that a new *formateur* is appointed.
